{
  "title": "Containerizing ETL Jobs Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer demonstrates how to leverage FastAPI, a modern web framework for building APIs in Python, to containerize ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) jobs using Docker and other related tools in Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI provides an efficient, user-friendly, and high-performance web framework for building APIs in Python 3.12+",
    "Docker is used to create lightweight, portable containers that encapsulate the application and its dependencies",
    "ETL jobs can be easily integrated with FastAPI to create an API that handles data extraction, transformation, and loading tasks",
    "FastAPI supports asynchronous programming, enabling efficient processing of ETL tasks",
    "The containerized FastAPI application can be easily deployed using popular orchestration tools like Kubernetes or Docker Swarm"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI, Depends\napp = FastAPI()\n\n# Define your ETL functions here\n\ndef etl(db: Database = Depends(get_db)):\n    # Perform the extraction, transformation, and loading tasks\n"
    },
    {
      "language": "Dockerfile",
      "code": "FROM python:3.12\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt ./requirements.txt\nRUN pip install -r requirements.txt\nCOPY . .\nCMD [\"python\", \"main.py\"]"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python version: 3.12+",
    "FastAPI version: latest (recommended using pip install fastapi[all])",
    "Docker version: >= 20.10.7"
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Ensure that all dependencies are listed in the requirements.txt file to avoid issues during container build",
    "Be aware of the specific Docker base image used (e.g., python:3.12) and its available packages, as some may differ from your local system",
    "Properly configure your API endpoints for security, such as using environment variables, authentication, or authorization"
  ]
}
